    <h2>Section A: Attempt any three questions.</h2><h3>Question 1</h3>
<div><p><p>Suppose you are working as an IT expert in the National Bank of Nepal, and working staff need five laptops for daily operation. Your manager asks you to present a proposal with time, cost, and objectives. Write a short proposal comparing the laptops available in the market of at least three renowned companies. Your proposal must include problems, solutions, and findings.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Proposal: Procurement of Laptops for Daily Operations</strong></p>
<p><strong>Objective:</strong> The objective of this proposal is to present suitable options for procuring five laptops to support the daily operations of the National Bank of Nepal&#8217;s working staff. This procurement aims to enhance efficiency, security, and productivity within the organization.</p>
<p><strong>Problem:</strong> Currently, the working staff at the National Bank of Nepal are facing challenges due to outdated hardware, resulting in decreased productivity and potential security risks. The existing laptops are slow, prone to frequent breakdowns, and lack modern features necessary for efficient banking operations. This situation hampers the bank&#8217;s ability to deliver timely and quality services to its customers.</p>
<p><strong>Solution:</strong> To address these challenges, we propose procuring five new laptops equipped with advanced features, robust security measures, and sufficient performance capabilities to support the bank&#8217;s daily operations effectively. We will explore options from renowned companies in the market to ensure reliability, durability, and compatibility with the bank&#8217;s existing systems and software.</p>
<p><strong>Findings:</strong> After thorough research and comparison, we have identified three renowned companies offering laptops suitable for the National Bank of Nepal:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li><strong>Dell Technologies:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Dell offers a range of business laptops known for their durability and performance.</li>
<li>Models such as the Dell Latitude series provide excellent security features and long battery life, ideal for banking operations.</li>
<li>Estimated cost per laptop: NPR 150,000</li>
<li>Delivery time: 2 weeks</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>HP (Hewlett-Packard):</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>HP laptops are recognized for their reliability and innovative design.</li>
<li>The HP EliteBook series offers advanced security features, including biometric authentication, to ensure data protection.</li>
<li>Estimated cost per laptop: NPR 160,000</li>
<li>Delivery time: 3 weeks</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Lenovo:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Lenovo ThinkPad series is popular among business users for its robust build quality and performance.</li>
<li>These laptops feature enhanced security options and ergonomic designs suitable for prolonged usage.</li>
<li>Estimated cost per laptop: NPR 155,000</li>
<li>Delivery time: 2-4 weeks</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Considering the requirements and budget of the National Bank of Nepal, we recommend procuring Dell Latitude laptops from Dell Technologies. These laptops offer a balance of performance, security, and cost-effectiveness, aligning well with the bank&#8217;s objectives. With a delivery time of 2 weeks and a competitive price of NPR 150,000 per laptop, Dell Latitude laptops will meet the immediate needs of the bank&#8217;s working staff while ensuring long-term reliability and efficiency.</p>
<p><strong>Conclusion:</strong> Procuring new laptops from Dell Technologies will address the existing challenges faced by the National Bank of Nepal&#8217;s working staff, improving productivity, security, and overall operational effectiveness. This investment demonstrates the bank&#8217;s commitment to leveraging technology for enhanced service delivery and customer satisfaction. We recommend swift action to initiate the procurement process and ensure timely deployment of the new laptops.</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 2</h3>
<div><p><p>As writing is not an overnight endeavor it follows a certain process. Discuss a process for technical writing.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>Technical writing, like any form of writing, follows a process to ensure clarity, accuracy, and effectiveness in communication. Here&#8217;s a structured process for technical writing:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li><strong>Understanding the Audience and Purpose:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Identify who will be reading the document (audience) and why it&#8217;s being written (purpose). Understand their knowledge level, needs, and expectations.</li>
<li>Tailor the content, language, and tone accordingly to ensure it resonates with the audience and fulfills the purpose effectively.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Research and Gathering Information:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Conduct thorough research on the topic to gather accurate and relevant information.</li>
<li>Consult reliable sources such as technical documents, manuals, experts, and subject matter specialists.</li>
<li>Organize and document the gathered information systematically for easy reference during the writing process.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Outline and Planning:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Create a structured outline outlining the main sections, sub-sections, and key points of the document.</li>
<li>Determine the logical flow of information to ensure coherence and readability.</li>
<li>Plan how to address the audience&#8217;s needs and achieve the document&#8217;s objectives within the outlined structure.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Writing Draft:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Start drafting the content based on the outlined structure, using clear and concise language.</li>
<li>Begin with an introduction that grabs the reader&#8217;s attention and provides an overview of the document&#8217;s purpose and content.</li>
<li>Develop the main body of the document with detailed explanations, instructions, descriptions, or analyses as per the topic.</li>
<li>Ensure each section flows logically into the next, maintaining coherence and continuity throughout the document.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Revision and Editing:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Review the draft for accuracy, completeness, and clarity.</li>
<li>Check for grammatical errors, typos, and inconsistencies in language and formatting.</li>
<li>Verify the accuracy of technical details, data, and references.</li>
<li>Seek feedback from peers, subject matter experts, or stakeholders and incorporate relevant suggestions for improvement.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Formatting and Presentation:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Format the document according to the prescribed style guide, including fonts, headings, spacing, and margins.</li>
<li>Use visual aids such as diagrams, tables, or charts to enhance understanding and illustrate complex concepts.</li>
<li>Ensure consistency in formatting, terminology, and style throughout the document.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Review and Approval:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Conduct a final review of the document to ensure it meets the intended objectives and quality standards.</li>
<li>Obtain necessary approvals from stakeholders or authorities before finalizing the document for distribution.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Publishing and Distribution:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Publish the final document in the appropriate format (e.g., print, online, PDF) and distribute it to the intended audience.</li>
<li>Provide instructions or guidance on how to access and use the document effectively.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Maintenance and Updates:</strong>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Periodically review and update the document to reflect changes in technology, regulations, or best practices.</li>
<li>Maintain version control and ensure the latest version is readily accessible to users.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<h3>Question 3</h3>
<div><p><p>You have watched one of your peer’s vlog (video blog) entries on the issue of “Blocked mind as a malfunction of communication”. What have you learned in addition to your ideas you learned from your teacher? How do your experiences in unblocking the mind differ from your peer? Write feedback to your peer’s vlog.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Feedback to Peer&#8217;s Vlog on &#8220;Blocked Mind as a Malfunction of Communication&#8221;</strong></p>
<p>Dear Abhisek,</p>
<p>I recently watched your vlog entry discussing the concept of a &#8220;Blocked Mind&#8221; as a malfunction of communication, and I must say, it was both thought-provoking and insightful. Your exploration of how communication breakdowns can lead to mental barriers resonated deeply with me, prompting further reflection on the topic.</p>
<p>One key takeaway from your vlog was the emphasis on the interconnectedness between effective communication and mental clarity. Your explanation of how misunderstandings, lack of clarity, and ineffective expression can create mental blocks shed light on the importance of clear and concise communication in fostering a healthy mindset.</p>
<p>Additionally, your insights into the role of active listening and empathy in overcoming communication barriers were particularly enlightening. Your examples and anecdotes effectively illustrated how genuine understanding and empathy can dissolve mental barriers and promote mutual understanding.</p>
<p>Reflecting on my own experiences, I&#8217;ve encountered similar challenges with communication-related mental blocks. However, one aspect that differs from my experiences is your emphasis on the transformative power of empathy. While I&#8217;ve recognized the importance of empathy in communication, your vlog inspired me to deepen my practice of empathetic listening and understanding, especially in moments of conflict or misunderstanding.</p>
<p>Furthermore, your vlog prompted me to consider the impact of non-verbal communication cues, such as body language and tone of voice, on mental blocks. While I&#8217;ve acknowledged the significance of these cues in communication, your insights reinforced their influence on mental clarity and perception.</p>
<p>In conclusion, your vlog on &#8220;Blocked Mind as a Malfunction of Communication&#8221; provided valuable insights into the complex relationship between communication and mental wellbeing. Your emphasis on empathy, active listening, and non-verbal cues as tools for overcoming communication barriers has left a lasting impression on me, inspiring me to further refine my communication skills and cultivate a clearer mindset.</p>
<p>Thank you for sharing your thoughts and experiences on this important topic.</p>
<p>Best regards,</p>
<p>Orion</p>
</div>
<h3>Question 4</h3>
<div><p><p>What are graphics? How are they used in technical writing?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Graphics</strong>, in the context of technical writing, refer to visual elements such as diagrams, charts, graphs, tables, illustrations, photographs, and other visual aids used to enhance the clarity, understanding, and effectiveness of written communication.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s how graphics are commonly used in technical writing:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li><strong>Visualization of Data and Information:</strong> Graphics are used to present data, statistics, and information in a visual format, making it easier for readers to interpret and analyze complex data sets. Charts, graphs, and tables are commonly employed to illustrate trends, comparisons, and relationships among variables.</li>
<li><strong>Clarification of Concepts and Processes:</strong> Graphics help clarify abstract or complex concepts, procedures, and processes by visually representing them in a step-by-step manner. Flowcharts, diagrams, and schematics are used to illustrate workflows, system architectures, algorithms, and procedures, facilitating understanding and retention of information.</li>
<li><strong>Enhancement of Descriptions and Explanations:</strong> Graphics complement textual descriptions and explanations by providing visual representations of objects, structures, mechanisms, or phenomena. Illustrations, diagrams, and photographs are used to depict physical components, parts, or features, aiding in comprehension and reference.</li>
<li><strong>Highlighting Key Points and Emphasizing Information:</strong> Graphics are used to highlight important points, key findings, or critical information within a document. Bold visuals, icons, or callout boxes draw attention to specific details, ensuring they are noticed and understood by the reader.</li>
<li><strong>Improvement of Document Layout and Organization:</strong> Graphics contribute to the overall layout and organization of a document by breaking up large blocks of text, improving readability, and maintaining reader engagement. Well-designed graphics create visual interest and structure within the document, guiding the reader through the content more effectively.</li>
<li><strong>Supporting Instruction and Training Materials:</strong> Graphics play a vital role in instructional and training materials by providing visual aids to support learning objectives. Diagrams, illustrations, and screenshots help learners visualize concepts, procedures, and tasks, enhancing comprehension and retention of information.</li>
<li><strong>Facilitating Localization and Translation:</strong> Graphics can help overcome language barriers and facilitate localization or translation of technical documents. Visual elements transcend language barriers, making it easier for international audiences to understand complex information without relying solely on textual content.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<h2>Section B: Attempt any ten questions.</h2><h3>Question 5</h3>
<div><p><p>Point out the differences between technical writing and academic writing.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><div class="table_wrapper" style="overflow-x:auto;"><table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 432px;">
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;"><strong>Technical Writing</strong></td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;"><strong>Academic Writing</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 168px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 168px;">The primary purpose of technical writing is to convey specific information or instructions related to a particular subject, product, process, or task. Technical documents aim to provide practical guidance, solve problems, or facilitate understanding for a specific audience.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 168px;">Academic writing aims to contribute to the body of knowledge within a specific academic discipline. It involves presenting original research, analyzing existing literature, forming arguments, and making scholarly contributions to a field of study.</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 168px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 168px;">The audience for technical writing is typically specialized and focused on a particular industry, profession, or task. Technical documents are designed for professionals, practitioners, or users who require specific information or instructions to perform their jobs effectively.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 168px;">The audience for academic writing is broader and includes scholars, researchers, students, and other academics interested in the subject matter. Academic papers are often peer-reviewed and intended for dissemination within the academic</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Technical writing tends to use clear, concise, and straightforward language to convey information effectively. It avoids jargon and complex terminology unless necessary for the intended audience. The style is typically objective and focused on delivering practical information or instructions.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Academic writing often employs formal language, specialized terminology, and complex sentence structures to convey depth of analysis and scholarly rigor. It may include theoretical frameworks, citations, and references to support arguments and claims.</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Technical documents are structured to prioritize usability and accessibility for the intended audience. They often include headings, bullet points, numbered lists, and visual aids such as diagrams or tables to organize information and facilitate comprehension.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Academic papers typically follow a standardized structure, such as introduction, literature review, methodology, results, discussion, and conclusion. They adhere to specific formatting guidelines (e.g., APA, MLA, Chicago) and include citations, references, footnotes, or endnotes to acknowledge sources and provide context.</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 24px;">
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">While technical writing may include references to external sources for credibility or additional information, it often prioritizes practical guidance over extensive citation. References are typically limited to sources directly relevant to the subject matter.</td>
<td style="width: 50%; text-align: center; height: 24px;">Academic papers require thorough citation and referencing of sources to support arguments, provide evidence, and acknowledge intellectual contributions. They adhere to specific citation styles and guidelines for accurately citing and referencing sources throughout the text.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
</div>
<h3>Question 6</h3>
<div><p><p>What is plagiarism? Why should we remain honest on borrowing other’s ideas?</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>Plagiarism</strong> refers to the act of using someone else&#8217;s ideas, words, or work without proper acknowledgment or attribution, thereby presenting them as one&#8217;s own. It can occur in various forms, including copying text verbatim, paraphrasing without citation, using someone else&#8217;s ideas or concepts without acknowledgment, and presenting fabricated data or research findings as original.</p>
<p>Remaining honest when borrowing others&#8217; ideas is essential for several reasons:</p>
<ol style="list-style-type:decimal;">
<li><strong>Intellectual Integrity:</strong> Honesty in academic and professional endeavors upholds intellectual integrity and ethical standards. Properly crediting the original creators of ideas or works demonstrates respect for their intellectual contributions and promotes a culture of academic and professional honesty.</li>
<li><strong>Academic and Professional Reputation:</strong> Plagiarism tarnishes one&#8217;s academic or professional reputation and credibility. Academic institutions, employers, and peers value originality, critical thinking, and the ability to engage with and build upon existing knowledge in an ethical manner.</li>
<li><strong>Legal and Ethical Obligations:</strong> Plagiarism violates copyright laws and intellectual property rights, which protect creators&#8217; ownership of their original works. Engaging in plagiarism can lead to legal consequences, including lawsuits, fines, and damage to one&#8217;s professional reputation.</li>
<li><strong>Quality of Work:</strong> Honest attribution and acknowledgment of sources contribute to the quality and credibility of one&#8217;s work. By incorporating diverse perspectives, insights, and research findings from other sources, individuals enrich their own work and enhance its depth, breadth, and authenticity.</li>
<li><strong>Personal Growth and Learning:</strong> Engaging with others&#8217; ideas in an honest and respectful manner fosters personal growth, critical thinking, and intellectual development. It encourages individuals to critically evaluate, synthesize, and build upon existing knowledge, leading to deeper understanding and innovation.</li>
<li><strong>Promotion of Knowledge Sharing:</strong> Honest acknowledgment of sources promotes knowledge sharing, collaboration, and dialogue within academic and professional communities. It acknowledges the interconnectedness of ideas and fosters a culture of openness, transparency, and mutual respect.</li>
</ol>
</div>
